==English==
===Etymology===
Corresponding to Old French [[coustillier]] ‘soldier armed with a [[coustille]] (a double-edged sword)’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'kʌstɹəl/

===Noun===
'''custrel'''
# a [[knight]]'s attendant or [[man-at-arms]]; a [[knave]]

